   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> compare Wizards to other casters </span><hr size=1> I  found the responces to the Wizards mana  regen  faster and wizard damage over one hours pretty lame  answers. I would like to see a full damage comparison for one hour against the other pure casters  including their pets. Have no clarity on. I bet Wizards would be the step children of damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/01 6:38:54 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: compare Wizards to other casters </span><hr size=1> It really depends on the situation, since most of the other pure casters get shafted ALMOST as much as we do.<br>
<br>
Ok, in a normal grouping situation, a wizard will generally be outdamaged by magicians and necros because of pets over and extended period.  BUT, remember that pathing sucks, and that pets can't be used while the group moves from camp to camp, and in many cases will wander off because of pathing.  Because of this, in most dungeons, pets are generally not wanted unless you stay in a camp the whole time, which is boring anyway.  <br>
<br>
Also, once the wizard hits level 55 or so, you have decent enough equipment where you can begin to really add to a group and not run out of mana as long as you get Clarity 2.  I did a test the other day, I get 13 casts of draught on a full bar of mana.  That's without Clarity or manasong, or anything like that, I just took a corpse at OS zone-in and started casting draught of fire on it.  At level 56 that's 688 damage per cast.<br>
<br>
So yea, the wizard DOES start to become a lot better, even with others in their mid 50s, the group DOES feel the presence of the wizard.  Snares, roots, and stuns added to DD, and with evac WILL make a good wizard desired for our damage output, as well as how well we can help a group.<br>
<br>
It's not ALL about the damage, though in large part it is.  Wiz epic helps as well, and the flowing thought items.  I know this wasn't the response you were looking for, but the fact is we keep wanting to be desired by groups.  That means for everything we do, not just damage.  I'd like to see some faster casting spells at the high level game as well for those times when fast casting means more than just doing damage.  Perhaps an 800 damage DD at 59 with a 2 second casting time.  This would be nice for those pesky greens and low blues that love to jump us.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 56 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/01 8:12:27 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: compare Wizards to other casters </span><hr size=1> No, Wizards will not outdamage the other casters over time.  Magicians, for example, can outdamage Wizards comfortably in a single combat, even in a few rounds of combat.  Druids are more hard pressed to do it quickly but do over time using DOTs and if they can charmed creatures.  Even an enchanter with a charmed monster can outdamage us (especially if you add in the extra damage done because of their speeding up tanks).  But I don't see the Wizard as being the most damaging OVER TIME.  We are supposed to be the fire QUICKLY, and its when we can't do THAT I think we find problems. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uplasmabolt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Plasma Bolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/01 11:02:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> dream world</span><hr size=1> I am level 59. I have not one piece of the wizard epic. Every time we are at last  guy  that drops the Wizzi epic piece a few wizards show up to roll on the piece. Thats if it drops. after about 15 Vs's 28 Traks  and Jumpies  Numerous Fears  not one piece. We are the Artillery of EQ. Not the Shield casters. Why then did they put a frigging Shield spell on epic. Should do same thing on others   like a summon food on cleric epic etc. It is Verrants policy to call us the artillery og EQ. Yet! They are scared to make us so. At level 59 I can solo one senitnet armor every 20 minutes if I cannot find a group  which is often. Flowing thought item?  get real! If I cannot get epic items the chances of getting the flowing thought one is about the same chance as verrant living up to their contract  with the paying customers  and making wizards the artillery of eq like the description in the manual. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usamadhibots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samadhi BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/01 12:14:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dream world</span><hr size=1> There are Nuke items in the game for our class that are MUCH easier to obtain than the Epic that cast reasonably-timed nukes. I like the Epic effect, it's a free manaskin. Once you get the Epic you'd be surprised how nice it is to have a Manaskin-type spell ready to cast with no regents whenever you want. I did not cast Manaskin before my Epic even when I would like to mainly because of the Peridot cost. With the epic I can throw up a skin whenever I want and have another 800ish HP. <p><P align=center>
Samadhi, 60<sup>th</sup> Sorcerer<BR><A href="http://www.drow.org/guild_roster/samadhi.shtml"> Profile</A> | <A href="http://www.drow.org">BotS</A> | <A 
href="mailto:nebulous@newnorth.net">E-mail</A></P>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/01 7:55:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dream world</span><hr size=1> I said this when the Epic was discovered and I've always thought it to be true.  The epic is a really nice item and the effect is a really great, powerful effect... for a robe.  For an epic item Wizards get I'd see any of these making a lot more sense for Wizards:<br>
<br>
A super lure spell that did like 400 and cast in 3 seconds (resistances like Banes).<br>
A channelling booster that made it nearly impossible to interrupt your casting.<br>
A Casting haste and constant Breeze effect so that you can cast your spells 30% faster.<br>
A Super Malise effect that lowers resistances by 50+ on fire, cold, and magic.<br>
A Blast enhancer that gives 25% more damage for no more mana to your blasts.<br>
A PBAE gun that fired off Thunderclap for no mana and a very quick or no delay casting time.<br>
<br>
All of these are possible to do (with some creative programming) but all make a HELL of a lot more sense based on the concept of the Wizard class and would make the class no more easy to solo, but much more friendly to groups.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualeolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aleolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/01 12:38:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> They give shamans the Jaundiced Bone Bracer, which does 260 damage in 8 seconds, yet they are afraid to give wizards their epic weapon any damage proc. Seems a little unbalanced, IMHO. And shamans get that proc on a bracer!<br>
-Aleolin Darkmoon<br>
PS: Grim, Shamans can already solo incredibly well with a JBB. If we had an epic with a 400 point lure in 3 seconds, we could become solo, mana-less demons. Just pointing that out. But the 25% dam. bonus or the haste on spells is brilliant. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uberylshadowhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beryl Shadowhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/01 12:43:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.unlv.edu/faculty/engstrom/images/bcard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dream world</span><hr size=1> Yep, the epic effect should be on my robe, that's for sure.  As for your solutions as to what should be on the epic, I like them.  VI won't becuase unlike what you stated, most of those would greatly help soloist.  Heh, Grim, free nukes, free breeze, free resistance debuff, faster casting, and increased damage reads like a soloist dream sheet.  <br>
<br>
I have always thought the epic should have a free uber nuke to it.  Something like a 1K lure spell with a 12 sec recast.  After all, who's going to have epics?  End game wizards.  VI really doesn't have worry about these folks going out and soloing up to 60, they already are there.  A 1K lure would be very useful to these folks, and would probably do away with the need for Bane spells, but VI is kind of clueless like that.<br>
<br>
The funny thing about the recent announcement about making wizzies more group friendly is how does VI go about doing this with a class.  Mages got CoH, Necros got a way to donate mana to clerics.  Oh yay!  I can't wait for my new porting spell or the chance to let some other player make use of my mana.  That'll get me in a group and make me happy as a clam...no wait, that'll really disappoint me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utygrav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tygrav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/01 3:34:41 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hem.passagen.se/cocker/tygrav.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dream world</span><hr size=1> I just must reply to this.<br>
