<br>
I like my mage, I like and respect wizards.  Work together to achieve an aim, not against one another.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhippolytahelios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyta Helios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/01 4:25:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> the JBB</span><hr size=1> &quot;They give shamans the Jaundiced Bone Bracer, which does 260 damage in 8 seconds, yet they are afraid to give wizards their epic weapon any damage proc. Seems a little unbalanced, IMHO.&quot;<br>
<br>
It very may well be... but at 55 (really earlier, but I gave away my JBB from 52 to 55 to someone who soloed more) 260 per 8 seconds isn't a nuke anymore... it's a sort of DoT.  Come to think of it, even a shaman's nuke at that level isn't much of a nuke... I tried to stop a runner with Ice Strike when I was soloing, and learned just how slow a 7-second cast blast is when you really need it (why yes, I did die <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
